# Memory Bridge

Claude Code stores per-project auto-memory at:

```
~/.claude/projects/-Users-williamteig-Documents-AppDev-<project-name>/memory/
```

Cursor does not auto-load this, but you should read from it when relevant. The files capture behavioural rules and project facts that evolved through prior conversations with Claude Code.

## When to read

- The user references something from a prior session ("remember when we...")
- Working on project state, approvals, or known blockers
- Before using any MCP that has a corresponding reference file in memory

## Global memory

Cross-project preferences and rules live at:

```
~/.claude/projects/-Users-williamteig-Documents-AppDev-Williams-2nd-Brain/memory/MEMORY.md
```

Read `MEMORY.md` first (index), then load specific files by name.

## Writing memory

Cursor cannot auto-save memory. If Will asks you to remember something durable:

1. Write the memory file to the correct path directly
2. Add a one-line entry to `MEMORY.md`
3. Tell Will what you saved so he can verify
